@node about
@title "About Landscaper"
@{b}                          ____________________________
                         /                            \
                        ||                            ||
                        || Landscaper by David McMinn ||
                        ||                            ||
                         \____________________________/@{ub}

   Whats it about?

      Landscaper is a small program which renders a 3D isometric picture of
    a plot of land. The variables associated with this plot of land can be
    altered by using the @{" Options " link opti} from the options window.

      It may not be of much use compared to the likes of Vista but hey -
    WHO CARES.

    When Landscaper was written, I had an old Archimedes program in mind which
    did exactly the same thing as Landscaper. Draw 3D landscapes. I set off
    on a journey of joy and frustration as I struggled to get it coded (in
    BLITZ BASIC ][).

     This program is freeware. It is freely distribuatble, and charges should
    not be more than the media supplied on, but the copyright remains with
    the author. If it is distributed, please include this file with the main
    program. And its not my fault if anything explodes, obviously your
    system with all the extras was too much for your PSU :)

    If any bugs are found, shout abuse at your Amiga and send bug reports
    to my internet address below. If you like this program and you use it
    then e-mail me.

    Landscaper was written by David McMinn.
