@NODE menu
@title "Pull them down..."
@{b}
    PROJECT MENU@{ub} :

     Load    - Loads a previously saved Landscaper map file. Select the name
               of the file from the requester that appears.

    Save map - Saves a previously generated map to a file on a disk. Select
               or type the name of the file in the requester that appears. If
               that file already exists, you will be asked if you want to
               overwrite it.

    Save IFF - Saves a previously viewed landscape to a file on a disk. Select
               or type the name of the file in the requester that appears. If
               that file already exists, you will be asked if yuo want to
               overwrite it.

        Info - Displays some info about the program.

        Quit - Exits from the program.

@{b}
    LANDSCAPE MENU@{ub} :

    @{"Options" link opti} - Gives access to the options window where rendering
               options can be altered.

    Generate - Generates a new map, using the current options settings. If at
               any time you wish to stop the generation process @{i}Stop@{ui}
               button in the main window and the indicator will disappear
               after a short time.

               @{b}@{u}Time stopped        Effect@{ub}@{uu}
                 Faulting      No map in memory
               Calc. Levels        Nothing
                 Drawing       No IFF in memory

               Rendering times vary according to the number fo faults, size
               and faulting method. On an unexpanded A1200, the rendering
               process took 9 mins 05 secs for a 100 fault, size of 160 with
               both methods on. These values are maximums with the exception
               of faults.

                The same options took 52 seconds to render on my 1260@50
               with 32Mb Fastram. He he he.

    Show map - Shows the last map that was calculated. This can be used to
               view a map that has just been loaded or at any other time
               @{b}@{i}except@{ub}@{ui} after pressing the stop button when
               during the faulting process.
@ENDNODE
